Name: megalencephalic leukoencephalopathy with subcortical cysts 1
Definition: A megalencephalic leukoencephalopathy with subcortical cysts characterized by early-onset macrocephaly and delayed-onset neurologic deterioration

Name: megalencephalic leukoencephalopathy with subcortical cysts 2B
Definition: A megalencephalic leukoencephalopathy with subcortical cysts characterized by infantile-onset macrocephaly and mildly delayed motor development associated with white matter abnormalities that improve with age

Name: megalencephalic leukoencephalopathy with subcortical cysts 2A
Definition: A megalencephalic leukoencephalopathy with subcortical cysts characterized by infantile-onset macrocephaly and later onset of motor deterioration
